description: **Building Exposure** identifies the vulnerability of buildings in low elevation coastal zones (LECZ) to coastal flooding under various climate change scenarios.​ - **Spatial coverage**: European coastal areas.​ - **Sources**: OpenStreetMap building data, CoCliCo inundation maps, regional sea level projections, and extreme weather data.​ - **Common usage**: Supports building exposure assessments, informs coastal resilience and adaptation planning, engages stakeholders with accessible data, and helps prioritize investments and strategic land-use decisions.​ ​More Info about the dataset: User Handbook

data.title: [not verified] PEP
data.description: [not verified] Population exposure projections for coastal flooding risk assessment.

summaries_descriptions.defense level: Policy-based coastal protection standards at the province level (NUTS2). High (low) defended: maximum (minimum) level of policy-based protection, if information is available. No defense: without protection (beyond what may be included in the DEM)
summaries_descriptions.return period: Frequency at which an extreme event of total water level (related to storms) is expected to occur on average.
summaries_descriptions.scenarios: Climate scenarios based on IPCC's Shared Socioeconomic Pathways (SSPs). High-end (if applicable) refers to P83 of SSP5-8.5, taking into account low-confidence processes. Other scenarios use the P50
summaries_descriptions.time: Time slice applied to the data. Either present-day (2010) or future state representing medium (2030 till 2050) and long term (2050 till 2100) outlook.
